<br>
Group consists of 49 mage and 52 druid...hoping to fear kite animals near zone...is this possible there? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulianadstaffborn2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lianad Staffborn2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(6/30/01 10:30:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=257.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Well</span><hr size=1> Well the way 99% of people get to WW is to just zone into SG with a druid and succor across the zone.  Succoring takes you almost literally right to the WW zone.  Once succored take the left tunnel behind the left walrus and bam you are in WW.<br>
<br>
As for a 52 druid and a mage fear kiting at zone I highly doubt it.  You might be able to take some drakes or some of the rhinos and mammoths, but the mammoths and rhinos arent naturally KOS, so its not always good to kill them.<br>
<br>
Those would really be the only things you even MIGHT have a chance at.  The only other wanderers are level 60 ice burrowers and the wandering giants.  WW is not a zone for 2 people =) Unless you are a 60 shaman and want to solo the naggy clone for bragging rights <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
