<br>
I would not advise fear kiting in WW.  There are two many KoS mobs, even if you're pro CoV, that could create many problems and wasted mana (ie. having to zone).<br>
<br>
However, while waiting on a CR in HoT earlier today, I saw a mastodan wandering near the entrance.  I decided to try soloing it and was very successful.  I'm 58th lvl and have the epic pet but I was naked.<br>
<br>
I'd say the two off you could probably pull it off but you'd have to spend <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> a lot</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of time and/or mana to do it and would definately need to chaincast pets while the druid kited it around in a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> small circle</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. (I had to nuke maybe 5-6 times at 805 dmg apiece and my pet was down to 50%)  Might be better to wait until the mage get's 51st lvl though.  At 49, you might see quite a few resists and your pets would die very quickly.  The 51st Earth pet might provide better results.<br>
<br>
I'd recommend burning woods over WW for your team - much easier kills. <p><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/jreiner/quassig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uevieofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evie of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 115<br> <font color=#333333>(7/2/01 10:50:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=257.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Guide to Western Wastes?</span><hr size=1> WW is not a place to solo/dual.  mobs have big assist aggro range, and right by the ww/sg zone line.... lots and lots of bad critters.  drakes quad for up to 200 dmg... 100+ cold AE... WW is good for raiding and raiding only.  <br>
